@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<section>
    <p>We are committed to protecting your personal data and respecting your privacy.</p>
    <p>This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and share your data.</p>
    <p>It applies to all users of our human management application.</p>
    <p>We process data in accordance with applicable data protection laws, including the GDPR.</p>
    <p>By using our services, you agree to the terms of this policy.</p>
    <p>We may update this policy periodically and will inform users of any significant changes.</p>
    <p>Continued use of the application after changes indicates your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
    <p>We collect personal data directly from users during registration and usage.</p>
    <p>Collected data may include names, contact information, job titles, and organization details.</p>
    <p>We also collect data related to user activity, preferences, and interactions within the app.</p>
    <p>Optional information may also be provided voluntarily for better personalization.</p>
    <p>We may use automated tools to collect usage data for analytics.</p>
    <p>All data is collected lawfully and transparently.</p>
    <p>We do not knowingly collect data from individuals under the age of 16 without parental consent.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>2. Data Uses</h2>
    <p>We use collected data to provide and improve our services.</p>
    <p>Data helps us personalize user experiences and manage user accounts.</p>
    <p>We use data to ensure the proper functioning of our platform and to prevent misuse.</p>
    <p>We may analyze data to identify trends and improve service quality.</p>
    <p>Data is used to communicate with users regarding their accounts or support needs.</p>
    <p>We may use data for legal compliance and to fulfill contractual obligations.</p>
    <p>Data may be anonymized and aggregated for research and statistical purposes.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>3. Data Location and Retention</h2>
    <p>Your data is stored on secure servers located within the European Economic Area (EEA).</p>
    <p>We ensure that storage providers meet industry security standards and comply with data protection laws.</p>
    <p>We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy.</p>
    <p>Once the data is no longer needed, it is securely deleted or anonymized.</p>
    <p>Some data may be retained longer for legal, compliance, or audit purposes.</p>
    <p>Data retention periods are reviewed regularly to ensure compliance.</p>
    <p>Users may request deletion of their data, subject to applicable retention requirements.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>4. Data Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent personal data to third parties.</p>
    <p>We may disclose data to trusted service providers who act on our behalf.</p>
    <p>These providers are contractually bound to protect data and use it only as instructed.</p>
    <p>We may share data if required by law or in response to legal requests.</p>
    <p>Disclosures may occur to protect our rights, safety, or the rights of others.</p>
    <p>In the event of a merger or acquisition, data may be transferred to the new entity.</p>
    <p>We maintain a strict access policy regarding who can view user data.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
    <p>Our website uses cookies to enhance user experience and provide essential functionality.</p>
    <p>Cookies help remember user preferences and login sessions.</p>
    <p>We use both session and persistent cookies for different purposes.</p>
    <p>Cookies may also be used for basic analytics and performance tracking.</p>
    <p>You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences.</p>
    <p>Disabling cookies may affect the functionality of the site.</p>
    <p>We do not use cookies to collect personally identifiable information without consent.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>6. Communications</h2>
    <p>We may contact users regarding important updates and notifications about their account.</p>
    <p>Users may receive emails about security alerts or policy changes.</p>
    <p>Marketing communications are only sent with user consent.</p>
    <p>Users can opt out of marketing messages at any time.</p>
    <p>We may communicate through in-app messages, emails, or push notifications.</p>
    <p>All communications are intended to support the user experience and platform integrity.</p>
    <p>We do not send unsolicited messages unrelated to our services.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement strong technical and organizational measures to protect user data.</p>
    <p>Access to personal data is limited to authorized personnel only.</p>
    <p>We use encryption, firewalls, and secure protocols to prevent unauthorized access.</p>
    <p>Regular security audits and assessments are conducted to maintain standards.</p>
    <p>We monitor our systems for potential vulnerabilities and respond to threats promptly.</p>
    <p>Employees receive training on data protection and privacy practices.</p>
    <p>In case of a data breach, we will notify affected users and relevant authorities in a timely manner.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>Users have the right to access, correct, or delete their personal data.</p>
    <p>Requests to exercise these rights can be submitted through our support channels.</p>
    <p>You may also request the restriction or objection to certain data uses.</p>
    <p>Users have the right to data portability where applicable.</p>
    <p>We respond to all privacy-related requests in accordance with legal timelines.</p>
    <p>If you believe your rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with a data protection authority.</p>
    <p>We are committed to helping users exercise their privacy rights fully and transparently.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>9. Roles and Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>We define clear roles for handling data privacy within our organization.</p>
    <p>Our Data Protection Officer oversees compliance and privacy-related matters.</p>
    <p>All staff members are responsible for following our data protection policies.</p>
    <p>Third-party vendors must adhere to our data protection standards.</p>
    <p>We conduct training and awareness programs for employees handling personal data.</p>
    <p>Internal audits are performed to ensure policy compliance.</p>
    <p>We maintain documentation of data processing activities to ensure accountability.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>10. Additional Notices & Contact Details</h2>
    <p>This policy may be supplemented by service-specific notices or terms.</p>
    <p>Users will be informed of any additional data practices specific to their use case.</p>
    <p>We encourage users to review these terms alongside this policy.</p>
    <p>If you have questions about our privacy practices, please contact us.</p>
    <p>You can reach our privacy team via the email address provided on our website.</p>
    <p>We aim to respond to inquiries within a reasonable time frame.</p>
    <p>Your feedback helps us continuously improve our privacy standards and services.</p>
</section>
